flowRoot.flowPara: Most of the app types are self-explanatory. However, we have two special app types you should know about.
"Jenkins" type will run a Jenkins CI instance you can share between all of your Jenkins-enabled apps.
"Raw" is for when you need the resources (Memory, CPU Cycles) of an extra app, but don't need a stack or a runtime installed.
Jenkins is a Continuous Integration server.
Continuous Integration is a way of running automated test suites. You can trigger tests based on code changes, or just when you feel like it.
Jenkins provides an interface to track and manage all of your CI jobs.
When you enable Jenkins on an app, it will create an additional Jenkins app automatically if you don't already have one.
